social_posts.post_text: Need a super easy dessert for the holidays? Grab a bag of my Holiday Spice Ann Potter Baking cookie mix and make thumbprint cookies filled with your choice of filling. Make the mix as directed, use a tablespoon or cookie scoop to dollop onto a sheet tray, press an indention into cookie with your thumb or spoon and bake for 12-14 minutes. Today I filled mine with chocolate ganache, and Jacks is incredibly excited to try one! You can order my mix online on my website, or pick up at some of my favorite local shops in Little Rock: @eggshells and @boxturtlehillcrest . . . . #decoratedcookies #sugarcookies #cookiedecorating #royalicing #diytop #cookieart #cookie #thebakefeed #instacookie #decoratedsugarcookies #foodnetworkcookies #annpotterbaking #foodart

Made these guys today too! Chocolate medallions are so delightful and wonderful for gifting. Melt @ghirardelli brand chocolate over a double boiler and add a medley of dried fruits, freeze dried fruit, nuts, and candies. let cool and then package for neighbors alongside cookies or other treats! Merry merry y’all! #. . . . #decoratedcookies #sugarcookies #cookiedecorating #royalicing #diytop #cookieart #cookie #thebakefeed #instacookie #decoratedsugarcookies #foodnetworkcookies #annpotterbaking #foodart

LOVE but make it look like a neon sign. Loved this design from last year! Basic Steps: outline, flood, while still wet, use thicker (honey texture) flood icing to write “love”, allow cookies to dry under a fan for that extra gloss, use outline icing (toothpaste consistency) to write over the background “LOVE”. #. . . . #decoratedcookies #sugarcookies #cookiedecorating #royalicing #valentinescookies #lovecookies #cookieart #cookie #thebakefeed #instacookie #decoratedsugarcookies #annpotterbaking

These temps have me dreaming of fishing. I grew up fly fishing for trout which will always have a special place in my heart but fishing with plastics on the Kings River for small mouth is right behind. I’ll have to share some of my fav fish in g highlights in my stories because I always have a few skeptics when I tell them how much I LOVE fishing and am capable of rigging up both types of rigs and *gasp* even taking taking the fish off! Are you a fisher-person?

Spring tennis has commenced! Worked on these last week for a fundraiser for Hope Lodge. The event was a blast- we were divided into teams and did a round robin style tournament playing best if 4 games to advance. My partner, Lisa, and I came in 4th out of the 16 teams which was a fun surprise! Tis the season for spring tennis! #tenniscookies #tenniscourtcookies #tennisculture #tennisreels #littlerockar #littlerockarkansas
